article.headline: Austin Peay 98, E. Illinois 71
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Drake Reed and Fernandez Lockett combined for 42 points as hot-shooting Austin Peay breezed to a 98-71 victory Thursday night over Eastern Illinois. The Governors (16-7, 13-2 Ohio Valley Conference) won for the 13th time in their last 14 games and stayed ahead in the OVC by shooting 66 percent from the floor. Reed scored 22 points and Lockett had 20 points and a game-high 10 rebounds. Landon Shipley added 18 points. Shipley was 6-of-7 from the field, Lockett 7-of-9 and Reed 8-of-11. Eastern Illinois (7-18, 3-13 OVC) was led by Mike Robinson and Romain Martin with 15 points each and Bobby Catchings with 11. The Governors took the lead for good with 5:21 left in the first half on a layup by Wes Channels to 29-27. It was 46-36 at the half. Austin Peay hit 11-of-18 3-pointers.
